About Us

We're an affiliated, not-for-profit student group established in August 2022.

We aim to provide a student-led platform that introduces its members to cyber security and advance their knowledge through workshops and activities, to legally and ethically improve the cyber security skills of our members, and to represent the university in cyber security competitions.

Our mission is to encourage interest in and advocate best practices in cyber security, aid learning and promote teamwork through competitive experiences.

Our Core Values are:

  • Integrity - maintain an ethical culture of trust, respect and open communication
  • Growth - continuous improvement not just individually and within the Club but also foster growth in the community through contribution and cooperation
  • Passion - nurture and cultivate passion about educating, leading, innovating, serving and making a positive impact.
